olive oil
2 Kumara
1 packet Baby Leaves
1 packet haloumi/grill cheese
1 packet Cherry Sauce
1 packet BBQ sauce
1 tbs plain flour
1 egg
½ packet panko breadcrumbs
2 Burger Bun
1 packet Deluxe Salad Mix
1 packet mayonnaise
1 packet chicken breast

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced. Peel kumara and cut into wedges.
• Place on a lined oven tray. Drizzle with olive oil, season with salt and toss to coat.
• Spread out evenly, then bake until tender, 20-25 minutes.

• Meanwhile, roughly chop baby leaves. Slice haloumi in half crossways to get 1 thin steak per person.
• In a small bowl, combine BBQ sauce and cherry sauce. Set aside.
• Place your hand flat on top of chicken breast and slice through horizontally to make two thin steaks.

• In a shallow bowl, add the plain flour and a pinch of salt. In a second shallow bowl, whisk the egg. In a third shallow bowl, place panko breadcrumbs.
• Dip haloumi slices into flour mixture, followed by the egg and finally in panko breadcrumbs. Set aside on a plate.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat. Cook chicken steaks until cooked through, 3-5 minutes each side (cook in batches if your pan is getting crowded). Transfer to a plate.
• Return frying pan to medium-high heat with enough olive oil to coat the base.
• Cook haloumi until golden brown, 2 minutes each side. Set aside on a paper towel-lined plate.

TIP: Chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink inside.

• Meanwhile, halve burger buns and bake directly on a wire oven rack until heated through, 2-3 minutes.
• In a large bowl, combine baby leaves, deluxe salad mix and mayonnaise. Season to taste.

• Spread burger tops and bases with some BBQ cherry sauce. Top with some creamy slaw, crumbed haloumi and chicken.
• Serve with kumara wedges. Enjoy!